   Then come back, by typing <SPC> one or more times.

   You have just learned a considerable number of commands.  If you want
to use one but have trouble remembering which, you should type ‘?’ (‘H’
in the stand-alone Info reader), which displays a brief list of
commands.  When you are finished looking at the list, make it go away by
typing <SPC> repeatedly.

>> Type ‘?’ (or ‘H’ in the stand-alone Info reader) now.
